<br />

<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=940" title="Permanent link to this article">I&#8217;m jazzed. Hope truly is on the way</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>Just finished watching the Kerry speech on the net and I&#8217;m jazzed.</p>

	<p>As far as sheer speech making goes, it didn&#8217;t hold a candle to Barak Obama&#8217;s awesome keynote address. But for John Kerry it was just perfect. (<a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A25678-2004Jul29.html">read it</a>|<a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/mmedia/politics/072904-27v.htm">watch it</a>)</p>

	<p>I was impressed with how absolutely ingenious his entry to the speech was: &#8220;I&#8217;m John Kerry and I&#8217;m reporting for duty.&#8221;</p>

	<p>Right there everything that has been said in the prior days in the convention had been wrapped up in a single phrase. Right there, patriotism and the urge to serve is fulfilled.</p>

	<p>The speech itself was surprising. Kerry, strongly defended about any weakness you could imagine the Democratic Party having. &#8220;Oh, they&#8217;re a party of the &#8216;60s.&#8217;&#8221; Yes, Kerry said and through it we provided civil rights, voting rights, womens rights and we&#8217;re back to finish the job. He always brought it back to the future and hope for the future.</p>

	<p>And my did he slam the Bush adminstration.</p>

	<p><blockquote>&#8220;I will be a commander in chief who will never mislead us into war. I will have a vice president who will not conduct secret meetings with polluters to rewrite our environmental laws. I will have a secretary of defense who will listen to the best advice of the military leaders. And I will appoint an attorney general who will uphold the Constitution of the United States.&#8221;</blockquote></p>

	<p>Amen. The opening has been played in the chess match. This will be interesting.</p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

<small>This entry was posted on Jul 30 by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a>. You can skip to the end and leave a response using the comment form.</small></p>

</div>

</div>




	

